annotation.TEXT: Looks like Missiles cap at 40. That should be way more than enough, since I don't use them very much.
Alright, there's the goal, so I'm good.
I could probably blow up Buzzy with a bomb, but he's gonna walk into the pit anyway.

Unfortunately, my previous save file was once again incompatable with this update, so I redid all of the levels up to here again with the same characters to end up with the same status I had for all of them at this point before (I think).
Whoop! Gotta be careful. If I take a single hit anywhere here, I likely won't be able to roast Bowser at the end of this level!
So, place your votes for who you want me to use in world 6! To be continued...
I guess I could try out my other weapons, like these arrows... assuming I can aim them right...
Ah, but the pipe right before the goal leads to a coin-filled, brick-filled, and icicle-filled bonus room.
Nuts. I was hoping that power up would restore at least one of the other upgrades, but nope. No Wave Beam and no Varia for me.
What the heck? A grayed-out missile? But, I can collect it. (It was a leftover item drop from my first trip through here, which I didn't collect then because I'd decided it was too risky.)

Anyway, the votes are shown up above, and the alt. skin votes included Skull Man (Bass) to be the coolest kid in school, Dark Samus, NES Tetrimino (Sophia III), and any girl character (Samus and certain skins of Luigi, Link, Simon, Mega Man, and Ryu).
And the Old Man gets to celebrate with a half-dozen fireworks!
Other votes included a sarcastic vote for a MLP character, a vote to terminate the sarcastic vote for a MLP character, and votes for Endless Eight, SMW Challenges, and Syobon Action.
Alright, it's boss... time?
Yeah, that hidden coin block down there shouldn't be surprising, because that's obviously how you'd normally reach the multi-coin block.
Hello, and welcome back to SMB Crossover! I hope you all had a nice Christmas! SMB Crossover apparently did, by getting another update, to version 3.1.2.
Maybe you guys should make more specific votes than for a color palette in the future.
Alright, now up next will either be Luigi or Samus, since there were two votes each for them.
Eat it, Bullet Bills, Sidesteppers, and... Bloopers? Sure, why not!
3-1 votes: 1
Well, at least Samus stayed alive this time, but that hit she took did rob her of a couple upgrades...
The RNG picked the Old Man. Not only is that the character I got the Exploding Rabbit item in 4-2 with, but it's the exact same skin too!
Okay, just a little further... Yes, I'm being extra cautious here.
Not quite. I've gotta get past this Hammer Bro. first. Good thing I'm armed to the teeth!

And here we have a split path, just like in the original SMB as well. For some reason, I always like to take the lower path in SMB's 5-4, even though there are fewer fire bars on the top path there. It must be because of the way they're rotating.

There was also a vote for any character with a red color palette, but that could be almost anyone due to alt. skins' different colors and palette swaps for things like the fire flower and Samus's Varia, so for the sake of simplicity, I just didn't count that vote at all.
Oh, man. Did I just rescue a Phanto? Also, Peach is apparently looking for "the Subcon". Should "Subcon" have a "the" in front of it?
I don't care if I miss a coin or two. My safety is more important.
Oh, no. Flying Cheepo Trouters! I just know I'm gonna eventually get beaned from behind at a bad time.
Yeah, I've gotta check this pipe. I hope the time spent doing so doesn't get me killed!
Bah. I hit it too early...
Now, if this is anything like the original SMB, there should be a super-ultra-mega-large fire bar right here... Yep!
Whoa, nearly got beaned from behind again. Also, that Beezo shooter's position isn't really much of a threat to me.
This part reminds me of the original SMB's 5-2... except for the addition of a multi-coin block here.
Well, that was fast. Also, did it only take me four fireballs to defeat him? Or did one of my shots from before the music change score a hit?
I'm gonna go over the top here, just like I often do in SMB as well.

There's another missile pickup, which is flashing like usual. I wonder why that other one wasn't flashing... Maybe due to the pipe transition? Well anyway, there's no need to go out of my way for missiles now, since I'm capped.
Alright, now it's Luigi's turn, but since one of the votes was for a female character, I'm gonna go with Peach. I believe I'll choose the SNES Peach this time.
I like how I can shoot the bricks to collect the coins in this room.
There's some Fighter Flies.
At least my Wave Beam one-shots these things.
SML's bonus game theme for the "hurry up" music? That's funny.
I believe I'll go with Samus for 5-3, and it's gonna be Dark Samus. I'll pick the one in the middle. (In hindsight, I should've saved Dark Samus for 5-4, but oh, well.)
I'm kind of glad I haven't been breaking balance lifts. I imagine that I would've been stuck if I broke this one when I first encountered it.
There's Modern Mario from Super Mario 3D World here...
Now, I'm a bit more suspicious of possible secrets. I wouldn't want to be killed by a horribly-placed hidden block.
Yeah, I should've saved Dark Samus for this level. Then, she wouldn't have lost her upgrades to a Cheepo, and her Varia would've protected me from the fire bars here.

Whoa! Good thing I wasn't fully committing to that jump up to the left, or that hidden 1-up block could've killed me! (Also, no. I don't believe I'm getting underwater physics while I'm in the water here.)
Oh, man. This could be really tricky. If a flame appears in the worst spot at the worst time, I could get roasted.
Alright, that'll do it for the levels I'll be playing today. However, I will point out that version 3.1.2 added a couple new skins...
I think I'll go with Random for 5-2, and... Oh, geez.
And, as far as I can tell, those are the only new skins (but correct me if I'm wrong), and I'm not going to spend forever going over every single skin again right now.
Argh! And there's that surprise bean from behind that I predicted! At least I didn't fall into the abyss, but my Wave Beam and Varia are gone.
Uh, oh. I'd better mind the ceiling as I jump to the elevator here.
Yep, since I have every upgrade, the power up block will just give me ammo now.
...And Modern Luigi, also from Super Mario 3D World here.
And, where did the game put me? Argh, I was afraid of this. It sent me back to the first pipe in the level I think. So that means... More flying Cheepos to deal with!
Votes for Google to change the comment system back: At least: 227,601.
Yeah, I decided to get that coin this time.
Alright, I made it past those fire bars. Now for a couple pits with Podoboos inhabiting them...
At least there are no Podoboos here.
This part's also reminiscent of the original SMB's 5-2, so I take it I'm near the end of the level?
Ooh, a star! I'll certainly take that!
Oh, did the Trouters stop? Good. (Probably because the goal's right there.)
